Rusty Russell <rusty@rustcorp.com.au> writes:
> +size_t strcspn(const char *s, const char *reject)
> +{
> +	const char *p;
> +	const char *r;
> +	size_t count = 0;
> +
> +	for (p = s; *p != '\0'; ++p) {
> +		for (r = reject; *r != '\0'; ++r) {
> +			if (*p == *r)
> +				return count;
> +		}
> +		++count;
> +	}
> +
> +	return count;
> +}	
How about "return p - s;" instead of "count"?
Regards, Olaf.
